The paper focuses on a user study of non-voice mobile phone usage by teens from an underserved urban community, which involves both quantitative and qualitative data collection methods. The study aims to understand the challenges of evaluating the usability of mobile systems and the unique values of mobile phones as a platform technology. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC), and Computation and Language (cs.CL).
